<subSubSection lastPageId="3" lastPageNumber="94" pageId="2" pageNumber="93" type="description">
<paragraph pageId="2" pageNumber="93">Description.</paragraph>
<paragraph lastPageId="3" lastPageNumber="94" pageId="2" pageNumber="93">
Perennial herbs. Roots fibrous. Stems procumbent, divaricately branched, 1-2 mm in diameter, up to 35 cm long, with scattered reddish dots. Leaves 4-6-verticillate, entire, sessile, narrowly ellipsoid, 5-12 
<normalizedToken originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
1.5-2.5 mm, base attenuate, apex acute. Flowers 5-merous, solitary in the axils of upper leaves, 5-8 mm in diameter. Pedicel 1.5-2.5 cm long. Sepals 5, lanceolate, 1.5-2 mm long, apex acute. Petals 5, white, pinkish towards the apex, lanceolate, 4-5 
<normalizedToken originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
1-2 mm, apex acute. Stamens 10, in 2 whorls, slightly shorter than the petals, antesepalous ones ca. 4 mm long, antepetalous ones ca. 3 mm long, inserted ca. 1 mm above the petal base, filaments 
<pageBreakToken pageId="3" pageNumber="94" start="start">white</pageBreakToken>
, 1.6-2.4 mm long, anthers ca. 0.4 mm long, reddish. Nectar scales spatulate, ca. 0.4 mm long. Carpels 5, white, suberect, adaxially minutely papillate, broadly ovoid, ca. 2 mm long, base united for ca. 0.2 mm, styles ca. 1.5 mm long. Follicles divergent, 0.8-1.1 mm long, with scattered reddish dots, seeds numerous, brown, ca. 0.5-1 mm long, papillate.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="3" pageNumber="94" type="phenology">
<paragraph pageId="3" pageNumber="94">Phenology.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="3" pageNumber="94">Flowering from early May to July, fruiting from August to October.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="3" pageNumber="94" type="distribution">
<paragraph pageId="3" pageNumber="94">Distribution and habitat.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="3" pageNumber="94">
<taxonomicName authorityName="Y. B. Wang" authorityYear="2019" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Crassulaceae" genus="Sedum" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Sedum ichangensis" order="Saxifragales" pageId="3" pageNumber="94" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="ichangensis">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="94">Sedum ichangensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is known from Longzhouping town of Changyang County, Gufu town of Xingshan County and Muyang River of Yiling County in Yichang City of western Hubei Province, central China (
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 3" captionStartId="F3" captionText="Figure 3. Distribution of Sedum ichangensis in Hubei province, central China. The three known localities are indicated with triangles." figureDoi="10.3897/phytokeys.132.35428.figure3" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/344046" pageId="3" pageNumber="94" tableDoi="10.3897/phytokeys.132.35428.figure3">Fig. 3</figureCitation>
). It grows on rocks of roadsides, especially in fissures filled with soil, at an elevation of ca. 100-280 m.
</paragraph>
<caption ID-Zenodo-Dep="3478763" doi="10.3897/phytokeys.132.35428.figure3" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/344046" pageId="3" pageNumber="94" start="Figure 3" startId="F3">
<paragraph pageId="3" pageNumber="94">
<emphasis bold="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="94">Figure 3.</emphasis>
Distribution of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Y. B. Wang" authorityYear="2019" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Crassulaceae" genus="Sedum" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Sedum ichangensis" order="Saxifragales" pageId="3" pageNumber="94" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="ichangensis">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="94">Sedum ichangensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in Hubei province, central China. The three known localities are indicated with triangles.
</paragraph>
</caption>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="3" pageNumber="94" type="chinese name">
<paragraph pageId="3" pageNumber="94">Chinese name.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="3" pageNumber="94">Yi-chang-jing-tian (宜昌景天).</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="3" pageNumber="94" type="etymology">
<paragraph pageId="3" pageNumber="94">Etymology.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="3" pageNumber="94">The specific epithet of this new species is dedicated to the Yichang city.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="3" pageNumber="94" type="taxonomic notes">
<paragraph pageId="3" pageNumber="94">Taxonomic notes.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="3" pageNumber="94">
<taxonomicName authorityName="Y. B. Wang" authorityYear="2019" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Crassulaceae" genus="Sedum" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Sedum ichangensis" order="Saxifragales" pageId="3" pageNumber="94" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="ichangensis">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="94">Sedum ichangensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
belongs to 
<taxonomicName class="Magnoliopsida" family="Crassulaceae" genus="Sedum" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" infraspecific-rank="sect." kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Sedum" order="Saxifragales" pageId="3" pageNumber="94" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="section" section="Filipes">Sedum sect. Filipes</taxonomicName>
on account of its carpels adaxially not gibbous, its spurless leaf base and its white flowers (
<bibRefCitation author="Fu, KJ" editor="Wu, ZY" journalOrPublisher="Science Press, Beijing and Missouri Botanical Garden Press, St Louis" pageId="5" pageNumber="96" pagination="202 - 268" refId="B6" refString="Fu, KJ, Ohba, H, 2001. Crassulaceae. In: Wu, ZY, Raven, PH, Eds., Flora of China, Volume 8. Science Press, Beijing and Missouri Botanical Garden Press, St Louis: 202 - 268" title="Crassulaceae." volumeTitle="Flora of China, Volume 8." year="2001">Fu and Ohba 2001</bibRefCitation>
). 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Y. B. Wang" authorityYear="2019" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Crassulaceae" genus="Sedum" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Sedum ichangensis" order="Saxifragales" pageId="3" pageNumber="94" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="ichangensis">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="94">Sedum ichangensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is a species easily identifiable by its floral, stem and leaf features. The new species resembles 
<taxonomicName class="Magnoliopsida" family="Crassulaceae" genus="S." higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="S. elatinoides" order="Saxifragales" pageId="3" pageNumber="94" phylum="Magnoliophyta" rank="species" species="elatinoides">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="94">S. elatinoides</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in the leaf characters, as well as the structure of the flowers. However, 
<taxonomicName class="Magnoliopsida" family="Crassulaceae" genus="S." higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="S. ichangensis" order="Saxifragales" pageId="3" pageNumber="94" phylum="Magnoliophyta" rank="species" species="ichangensis">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="94">S. ichangensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
differs from 
<taxonomicName class="Magnoliopsida" family="Crassulaceae" genus="S." higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="S. elatinoides" order="Saxifragales" pageId="3" pageNumber="94" phylum="Magnoliophyta" rank="species" species="elatinoides">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="94">S. elatinoides</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in its perennial habit with branched stems and its solitary flowers. 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Y. B. Wang" authorityYear="2019" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Crassulaceae" genus="Sedum" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Sedum ichangensis" order="Saxifragales" pageId="3" pageNumber="94" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="ichangensis">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="94">Sedum ichangensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
differs from 
<taxonomicName class="Magnoliopsida" family="Crassulaceae" genus="S." higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="S. rosthornianum" order="Saxifragales" pageId="3" pageNumber="94" phylum="Magnoliophyta" rank="species" species="rosthornianum">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="94">S. rosthornianum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in its much branched, decumbent stems, entire leaf margins and its solitary flowers. Here, we provide photographs (
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 1" captionStartId="F1" captionText="Figure 1. Sedum ichangensis Y. B. Wang from type locality A habitat B flowering stems C flower D unripe follicles E carpels with style." figureDoi="10.3897/phytokeys.132.35428.figure1" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/344044" pageId="3" pageNumber="94" tableDoi="10.3897/phytokeys.132.35428.figure1">Fig. 1</figureCitation>
), line drawings (
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 2" captionStartId="F2" captionText="Figure 2. Sedum ichangensis Y. B. Wang, sp. nov. A habit B flower C carpels D single carpel." figureDoi="10.3897/phytokeys.132.35428.figure2" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/344045" pageId="3" pageNumber="94" tableDoi="10.3897/phytokeys.132.35428.figure2">Fig. 2</figureCitation>
) and a detailed morphological comparison (Table 
<tableCitation captionStart="Table 1" captionStartId="T1" captionText="Table 1. Morphological comparison between Sedum ichangensis and related species." httpUri="http://table.plazi.org/id/D05C79B17B9724A7CEBBE060D1A6EABA" pageId="3" pageNumber="94" tableUuid="D05C79B17B9724A7CEBBE060D1A6EABA">1</tableCitation>
), as well as a key to the species of 
<taxonomicName class="Magnoliopsida" family="Crassulaceae" genus="Sedum" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" infraspecific-rank="sect." kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Sedum" order="Saxifragales" pageId="3" pageNumber="94" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="section" section="Filipes">Sedum sect. Filipes</taxonomicName>
in China to facilitate its identification.
</paragraph>
